title: PML-N’s Zahir Khan wins PK-78 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 09 (APP): Pakistan Muslim League Nawaz (PML-N) candidate Zahir Khan has won the Khyber Pakhtunkhwa Assembly election from PK-78, Peshawar-VII by securing 22,559 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was an Independent candidate Muhammad Asim Khan who bagged 17,125 votes.
Overall voters’ turn-out remained 44.50 per cent.
